    "# Zameen.com Web Scraper - Full Feature Collection\n",
    "**Student:** Menahil Suleman
    "\n",
    "**Task:** CLO-1 Data Acquisition and Web Scraping\n",
    "\n",
    "This scraper runs in two phases:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Phase 1:** Collect listing URLs and basic fields from search result pages\n",
    "- **Phase 2:** Visit each listing detail page to collect extended features\n",
    "\n",
    "Target: 300 listings from Islamabad with full feature extraction."
   ],
   "id": "46c319bd2ec03c9b"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Problem Statement\n\nReal estate pricing in Pakistan is largely informal and opaque. Buyers and sellers rely on personal contacts or rough estimates, making it difficult to assess whether a listed price is fair. This project addresses that gap by building a machine learning-based house price prediction system trained on real property listings scraped from Zameen.com.\n\nThe system takes four inputs (property area, number of bedrooms, number of bathrooms, and location) and outputs an estimated market price in PKR. This provides an objective, data-driven reference point for buyers, sellers, and investors in the Islamabad real estate market."
   ],
   "id": "4c003807f12a7277"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Dataset Description\n\nThe dataset is collected by scraping live property listings from [Zameen.com](https://www.zameen.com), Pakistan's largest real estate platform.\n\n| Attribute | Detail |\n|---|---|\n| Source | Zameen.com (scraped via BeautifulSoup) |\n| City | Islamabad only |\n| Target Listings | 300 |\n| Features from Search Page | city, location, price, bedrooms, bathrooms, size, listing URL |\n| Features from Detail Page | property type, built year, parking spaces, servant quarters, store rooms, kitchens, drawing rooms |\n| Target Variable | price\\_pkr (house price in Pakistani Rupees) |\n| Format | CSV |\n\n**Note:** Not all listings populate every field. Missing values in extra features are handled during preprocessing."
   ],
   "id": "414fc8877f462231"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Challenges Faced During Implementation\n\n**1. Two-phase scraping required:** Basic fields (price, size, beds, baths) are shown on search cards. Extended features (property type, built year, parking, servant quarters, etc.) only appear on individual listing detail pages. This required a second HTTP request per listing.\n\n**2. ARIA label selectors used for stability:** Zameen.com uses dynamic CSS class names that change between deployments. The scraper uses `aria-label` attributes instead, which remain consistent across updates.\n\n**3. Inconsistent size formats:** Property sizes are listed in Marla, Kanal, and Sq. Yd. A converter function normalises all to square feet.\n\n**4. Rate limiting:** A 3 second delay is applied between detail page requests to avoid IP blocking.\n\n**5. Sparse extra fields:** Many listings do not fill in all optional fields. Servant quarters, store rooms, kitchens, and drawing rooms are frequently missing and will be handled during preprocessing.\n\n**6. Outliers:** A small number of listings have extreme prices or sizes. These are handled with 99th percentile capping during preprocessing."
   ],
   "id": "8403ef1d2eaf5d3d"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
